GEU Events - MySQL Project Setup

Yeh instructions app.py ko aapke local MySQL server ke saath chalaane ke liye hain.

Step 1: MySQL Workbench Mein Database Banayein

Apna MySQL Workbench kholein aur local connection se login karein.

Ek naya query tab kholein aur sirf yeh ek command chalayein:

CREATE DATABASE event_system;


IMPORTANT: Aapko database.sql file (jisme CREATE TABLE likha hai) run karne ki zaroorat nahi hai. app.py yeh kaam khud karega.

Step 2: Terminal Mein Project Setup Karein

Apna Windows Terminal kholein aur project folder mein jaayein:

cd Desktop\Event_Management


Virtual environment banayein (agar nahi bana hai):

python -m venv venv


Environment ko activate karein:

.\venv\Scripts\activate


(Aapke prompt ke shuru mein (venv) dikhna chahiye.)

Step 3: Saari Libraries Install Karein

Jab (venv) active ho, yeh command chalayein:

pip install Flask Flask-SQLAlchemy Flask-Cors Flask-Bcrypt PyJWT PyMySQL


(PyMySQL driver hai jo Python ko MySQL se baat karne deta hai.)

Step 4: Server Run Karein

Libraries install hone ke baad, server run karein:

python app.py


Aapko terminal mein yeh dikhna chahiye (bina kisi red error ke):

Default admin user (admin@geu.ac.in / admin123) created.
Default 'GEU Auditorium' venue created.
Database tables checked and initial data added.
 * Running on [http://127.0.0.1:5000/](http://127.0.0.1:5000/)


Apna browser kholein aur http://127.0.0.1:5000/ par jaayein.

Aapka poora advanced application taiyaar hai!